  "contentHtml": "<p><a href=\"https://samenright.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Sam Enright</a> emails me:</p>\n<blockquote><p>In the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irishtimes.com%2Fireland%2F2023%2F05%2F30%2Fcensus-2022-number-of-non-irish-citizens-usually-resident-in-ireland-rises-to-12-per-cent-of-population%2F&amp;data=05%7C02%7Ctcowen%40gmu.edu%7C797e5123e45f49fb429c08decac4a476%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C639171143099886332%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=xxXq6evNIwpaWgv%2BH4neB7203P8in%2BIHiGFCBWyXuuw%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">most recent census</a>&nbsp;(2022), 1,017,437 people in Ireland were born abroad. Even if you&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stats.gov.cn%2Fenglish%2FPressRelease%2F202105%2Ft20210510_1817193.html&amp;data=05%7C02%7Ctcowen%40gmu.edu%7C797e5123e45f49fb429c08decac4a476%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C639171143099921772%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=G9K0J74%2BBUJV80T%2FwyuJWBZgUSFIbwha3Sf6bzS0GpQ%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">classify&nbsp;people from Taiwan</a>&nbsp;as “foreigners”, there are 845,697&nbsp;+&nbsp;157,886 =&nbsp;1,003,583 immigrants to China. There are now more foreigners in Ireland than in China&nbsp;in absolute terms,&nbsp;despite having a population that is 260 times smaller.</p></blockquote>",
